The paper deals with a conjecture related to lower bounds on the size of log-depth boolean circuits computing linear operators, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of completion of matrices and semi-linear equations suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The mention of non-linear codes and their comparison to linear ones points towards discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and coding theory (cs.CG).
